Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea, filed.

Defendant Trevelle L Walk in court.  Attorney Michael Jude in court for Trevelle L Walk.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Plea and Sentencing Hearing. State filed an amended information;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Parties have reached a resolution. State placed negotiations on the record. Defense counsel and defendant confirms. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 and 2: Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY to the amended information.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea. Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 
 

Case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 11.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 16, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Defense requested plea and sentencing date.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea and sentencing in Branch 11.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 30, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
